entries.npc_11: Nothing wrong with weird.  What worries me is you.  Right?
entries.npc_10: I'm sure you can.  See what my people have and we'll see how you do.  If you're really any good you won't need my help finding them.
entries.npc_5: There's not just one.  There's tons of jobs.  But I need good people.  Not just anybody off the street that strikes up a conversation.
entries.npc_9: Then find one of my people and see what kind of work we have.  You'll know them when you see them.  Or you won't.  You know?
entries.npc_8: You don't seem to know what we're talking about so I'm going to assume you already have another job and just go on about my business.
entries.npc_4: You could be.  You seem fit enough.  Are you?  Are you any good at all?
entries.npc_3: Too bad.  I got a lot of work and no good people.
entries.npc_7: Anyone I don't know is a stranger.  You know?
entries.npc_6: Exactly.  And if you don't know then you can't know can you?  So you should move on, before you know too much.
entries.npc_2: If you don't know then you probably don't want it.  Not the kind of work for strangers or those who don't know.  Ya know?
entries.npc_1: Plenty to do on Corellia.  Easier than working on Naboo.  Safer than Tatooine.  Did you come looking for work?
